{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff53cf5b-c760-4a0f-9efc-da2e46617d83","content":"The official MCP Registry is the **[mcp-registry](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry)** repo on GitHub. To register your server:\n\n1. **Fork** `modelcontextprotocol/registry` on GitHub.\n2. **Add a JSON file** for your server under the `servers/` directory (e.g., `servers/your-server-name.json`) following the registry's schema — typically including name, description, repository URL, install instructions, and transport type.\n3. **Open a Pull Request** against the main branch.\n4. The maintainers will review and merge it.\n\nCheck the repo's `README.md` and existing entries in `servers/` for the exact JSON schema and any contribution guidelines:\n\n👉 **https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry**\n\nSince your server is a NuGet package, make sure to include the `dotnet tool install` or `dotnet run` command as the install/run instruction so users know how to get it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5274215f-7741-40e7-8497-f2c2bc3706f0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know about this process.\n\nLet me check if there's any relevant information in the current repository that might help, since the repository seems to contain skill plugins and MCP-related tooling.\n\nActually, let me first check what's in the current working directory and if there's any MCP registry documentation.","outputTokens":358,"requestId":"5034:BAAC4:D1708B:F1C5F6:69F2ABC2"},"id":"ee1268c9-0b9d-48df-9a13-eb76a2413e37","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:09:33.895Z","parentId":"8447dacb-0358-433b-b584-5a374a663335"}
